{"key":"post-10363364","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10363364</id>\n<content>That's too wet.&amp;nbsp; If you're going to use the pillow case method, you must squeeze the water out.&amp;nbsp; Not enough will drain by gravity.&amp;nbsp; When ready to spawn, no more than a few drops should come out when you squeeze a handful.&amp;nbsp; Substrates made on the dry side colonize much faster than wet ones.&amp;nbsp; Remember, you can always dunk prior to first flush if necessary to load up the moisture, but it shouldn't be wet during colonization.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hay generally isn't suitable for bulk substrates because of the seeds in it, which tend to mold.&amp;nbsp; Use straw next time.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10363372</next>\n<prev>10362683</prev>\n<first>10361370</first>\n<last>10365523</last>\n<when>1242743905</when>\n<utime>05/19/09 05:38 PM</utime>\n</post>"}